{{Infobox organization | formation = {{start date and age|1994|03|24}} | purpose = [[Humanitarian Aid]] | headquarters = [[Andorra la Vella]] | leader_title = President | leader_name = Josep Duró Vidal | name = Andorran Red Cross | native_name = Creu Roja Andorrana | website = http://www.creuroja.ad/ | region = [[Andorra]] | revenue = [[Euro|€]]1,760,759.25 (2013)<ref name="adaudit">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ifrc.org/en/who-we-are/data-explorer/|title=IFRC Data Explorer}}</ref> }}
The '''Andorran Red Cross''' ([[Catalan language|Catalan]]: ''Creu Roja Andorrana'') is a humanitarian organization that provides emergency assistance, disaster relief and education within [[Andorra]]. The organization was founded in 1980, and was officially recognized as the 162nd National Society member of the [[International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies]] on March 24, 1994. Its headquarters are in [[Andorra la Vella]].
