{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Electronic and Postal Communications Authority |type = |nativename = Autoriteti i Komunikimeve Elektronike dhe Postare |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = Autoriteti i Komunikimeve Elektronike dhe Postare logo.svg |logo_width = 125px |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} OR {{Start date and years ago|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = Albania |headquarters = Rr.Reshit Çollaku, Nr.43, Tirana, Albania |chief1_name = Ilir Zela |chief1_position = Chairman of Steering Board |parent_agency = |website = {{URL|www.akep.al}} }} The '''Electronic and Postal Communications Authority''' ({{lang-al|Autoriteti i Komunikimeve Elektronike dhe Postare}} or ''AKEP'') is the [[Telecommunications in Albania|telecommunications]] [[Regulatory agency|regulator]] for [[Albania]]. It administers the ''Law on Electronic Communications''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.setimes.com/cocoon/setimes/xhtml/en_GB/newsbriefs/setimes/newsbriefs/2011/03/08/nb-12 |title=Communication authority criticises monopoly in Albanian landline telephony |date=8 March 2011 |work=SETimes |accessdate=31 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.internationallawoffice.com/newsletters/detail.aspx?g=15d27e82-9eec-47ab-a30d-d4ff3bdb4206 |title=General and individual authorizations under new Law on Electronic Communications |last=Muçaj |first=Enkelejda |author2=Sajmir Dautaj |date=24 February 2010 |publisher=International Law Office |accessdate=31 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telecompaper.com/news/plus-calls-on-govt-to-issue-more-3g-licences |title=Plus calls on govt to issue more 3G licences |date=21 September 2011 |work=TelecomPaper |quote=OTE's AMC was the highest bidder in the tender recently organised by the Electronic and Postal Communications Authority (AKEP) to grant a second 3G mobile licence in the market. |accessdate=31 October 2012}}</ref> It also manages the '''[[.al]]''' geographic [[top-level domain]].
Its office is located at Rr.Reshit Çollaku, Nr.43 in [[Tirana]].
