[[File:Azeri tribe Terekeme.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Azeris|Azeri]] tribe [[Terekeme]] Postcard of the [[Russian Empire]]]] The '''Terekeme people''' ({{lang-az|Tərəkəmə}}) are an ethnic group of [[Azerbaijanis]]<ref>{{cite book|author= [[Sakinat Hajiyeva]]|title = Дагестанские терекеменцы: XIX - начало XX в|publisher = Наука|year = 1990|page = 3|isbn =5-02-016761-4|ref=Hajiyeva 1990}}</ref> who live in [[Dagestan]] and in some southern regions of [[Azerbaijan]] as well as [[Turkey]]. The population is mainly engaged in cattle breeding and is most often seen as [[nomads]].{{sfn|Hajiyeva 1990|pp=8-9}}
The Terekemes are Shiite and Sunni Muslims and speak the Terekeme dialect of [[Azerbaijani language]].
